{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee2c037e-05bf-4fb8-a615-f4aaf49b1756","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively (note the `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`). It uses `--treenode-filter` for filtering, not VSTest `--filter`. The treenode pattern is `/assembly/namespace/class/test`.\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThe `--` separates `dotnet test` args from MTP args. The wildcards match any assembly, namespace, and test method — filtering only by class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e978f5f-6189-45a7-87d1-a6c788419168","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit with MTP, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit on MTP, the class filter uses `--treenode-filter`:\n\n```\ndotnet run --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nOr with `dotnet test`, TUnit projects using MTP need:\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName~SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nWait, let me think more carefully. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The project has `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` which confirms MTP runner.\n\n\nFor TUnit on MTP, filtering is done via `--treenode-filter` with the pattern `/assembly/namespace/class/test`. I can use either `dotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"` or `dotnet run -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"` to filter by the class name.","outputTokens":522,"requestId":"7C13:16BC0E:15A9A42:186C832:69F948CC"},"id":"2a4523c0-8f1f-4050-8a45-f02ed7fece83","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:33:11.412Z","parentId":"f289f98b-2ba7-4337-86c9-c4b686b12f7d"}
